In this article, President Biden gives a brief statement regarding the Omicron variant and the COVID-19 vaccination efforts. He mentions that preliminary lab data from Pfizer shows that three doses of the Pfizer vaccine protect against the Omicron variant. He also announces that 16- and 17-year-olds are now eligible for boosters. Biden encourages those who were vaccinated six months ago to get their booster shots, as 50 million people have already done so. He highlights that America is making progress with 200 million people having received two vaccine doses and having vaccinated more children than any other country. Biden expresses optimism that the country will get through the pandemic and concludes by mentioning that he is about to receive a briefing from his COVID team.